[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- coordinator and specialist registry contracts[39m                                 [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- delegation plans[39m                                                              [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- synthesis interfaces[39m                                                          [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- assistant-level orchestration semantics[39m                                       [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m## Expected Consumer Role[39m                                                       [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mA product should import this package when one assistant should orchestrate [39m     [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mmultiple internal specialists.[39m                                                  [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mIllustrative usage target:[39m                                                      [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m```ts[39m                                                                           [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mimport { createCoordinator } from "@relay-assistant/coordination";[39m              [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m```[39m                                                                             [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m## What Stays Outside[39m                                                           [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- fixed specialist lineups for a specific product[39m                               [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- product-specific dispatch heuristics[39m                                          [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- domain workflows that do not generalize[39m                                       [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m---PACKAGE BOUNDARY MAP---[39m                                                      [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m# Package Boundary Map[39m                                                          [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mDate: 2026-04-11[39m                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m## Purpose[39m                                                                      [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mThis document defines what belongs in:[39m                                          [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Relay foundation repos[39m                                                        [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- `relay-agent-assistant` OSS SDK packages[39m                                      [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- product repositories such as Sage, MSD, and NightCTO[39m                          [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mThe goal is to prevent duplicate assistant-runtime work while avoiding leakage [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mof transport infrastructure or product-specific behavior into the wrong layer.[39m  [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m## Boundary Rule[39m                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mUse this rule first:[39m                                                            [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- if the capability is transport, auth, scheduling substrate, or low-level [39m     [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231maction dispatch, keep it in Relay foundation[39m                                    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- if the capability assumes an assistant identity, memory model, session contin[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m… +1552 lines …[39m                                                                 [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mivity and how it must not take ownership of routing, memory, or surfaces[39m        [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m5. specify the minimum tests to write now[39m                                       [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mEnd the document with V1_COORDINATION_IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN_READY.[39m                [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m---[39m                                                                             [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mSTEP OWNER CONTRACT:[39m                                                            [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- You are the accountable owner for step "lead-coordination-plan".[39m              [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- If you delegate, you must still verify completion yourself.[39m                   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Preferred final decision format:[39m                                              [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  OWNER_DECISION: <one of COMPLETE, INCOMPLETE_RETRY, INCOMPLETE_FAIL, [39m         [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mNEEDS_CLARIFICATION>[39m                                                            [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  REASON: <one sentence>[39m                                                        [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Legacy completion marker still supported: [39m                                    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mSTEP_COMPLETE:lead-coordination-plan[39m                                            [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Then self-terminate immediately with /exit.[39m                                   [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m---[39m                                                                             [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mAUTONOMOUS DELEGATION — READ THIS BEFORE STARTING:[39m                              [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mYou have approximately 60 minutes before this step times out. Plan accordingly [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m— delegate early if the work is substantial.[39m                                    [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mBefore diving in, assess whether this task is too large or complex for a single[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m agent. If it involves multiple independent subtasks, touches many files, or [39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mcould take a long time, you should break it down and delegate to helper agents [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mto avoid timeouts.[39m                                                              [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mOption 1 — Spawn relay agents (for real parallel coding work):[39m                  [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  - mcp__relaycast__agent_add(name="helper-1", cli="claude", task="Specific [39m    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231msubtask description")[39m                                                           [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  - Coordinate via mcp__relaycast__message_dm_send(to="helper-1", text="...")[39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  - Check on them with mcp__relaycast__message_inbox_check()[39m                    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  - Clean up when done: mcp__relaycast__agent_remove(name="helper-1")[39m           [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mOption 2 — Use built-in sub-agents (Task tool) for research or scoped work:[39m     [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  - Good for exploring code, reading files, or making targeted changes[39m          [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  - Can run multiple sub-agents in parallel[39m                                     [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mGuidelines:[39m                                                                     [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- You are the lead — delegate but stay in control, track progress, integrate [39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mresults[39m                                                                         [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Give each helper a clear, self-contained task with enough context to work [39m    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mindependently[39m                                                                   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- For simple or quick work, just do it yourself — don't over-delegate[39m           [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Always release spawned relay agents when their work is complete[39m               [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- When spawning non-claude agents (codex, gemini, etc.), prepend to their task:[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  "RELAY SETUP: First call register(name='<exact-agent-name>') before any other[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m relay tool."[39m                                                                   [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m---[39m                                                                             [49m
